    <details>
        <description>
	    A "bank" of standard feedback phrases are defined for a particular assignment.
	    During the assessment of each student's work, relevant phrases from this bank are chosen
	    as feedback. This reduces the amount of time spent typing up feedback, whilst at the
	    same time ensuring a reasonable amount of relevant writting feedback material.
	    Often combined with some amount of manual text entry to provide some custom feedback.
	</description>
        <applicability>
	    Works well with convergent assignments, where submissions tend towards a standard solution.
	    Useful approach when students have a tendancy to make common mistakes.
	    Particularly useful for large cohorts of students where economies of scale can take effect.
	</applicability>
        <consequences>
	    Feedback can feel impersonal and generic, leading students to undervalue the comments made.
	</consequences>
    </details>
    
